---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const title = 'About — Easy1099Tax';
const description = 'About Easy1099Tax: a free, fast, private self-employment and 1099 tax calculator for U.S. freelancers, gig workers, and independent contractors.';
---
<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-14 prose-slate">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900">About Easy1099Tax</h1>
    <p class="mt-5 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Easy1099Tax is a free online calculator that helps self-employed people in the United States — freelancers, gig workers, independent contractors, and sole proprietors — estimate the taxes they owe on their 1099 income. We built it because the self-employment tax math (the 15.3% rate, the 92.35% adjustment, the Social Security wage cap, the half-SE-tax deduction, quarterly estimates) is genuinely confusing, and most existing tools either bury it behind a sign-up or push you toward paid software.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">What we believe</h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-slate-600">
      <li><b>It should be instant and free.</b> No account, no email, no upsell. You type your numbers, you see your estimate.</li>
      <li><b>It should be private.</b> Every calculation runs entirely in your browser. Your income figures are never sent to a server or stored.</li>
      <li><b>It should be accurate and honest.</b> We base the math on IRS and SSA primary sources, use the final 2025 and 2026 federal figures, and update them as the IRS releases each year's numbers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">How we keep it current</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Tax figures change every year. We track the IRS, the Social Security Administration, and published inflation adjustments, and update the calculator's rates, wage bases, and brackets as official numbers are released. Where a value is not yet final, we mark it as an estimate.</p>

    <div class="mt-10 rounded-2xl bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-5 text-sm text-slate-500">
      <b class="text-slate-700">Important:</b> Easy1099Tax provides estimates for informational purposes only and is not a substitute for professional tax advice. See our <a href="/terms" class="text-indigo-600 underline">Terms</a> and consult a qualified tax professional for your specific situation.
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
